This paper is about personalizing search results, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper proposes a hierarchical recurrent neural network (RNN) with query-aware attention to exploit sequential information and generate user profiles. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of RNNs and attention mechanisms also suggests that this paper could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves analyzing user behavior and search history, which could be considered a topic in social computing (cs.SI).
